| "Cross-fixture ceiling is mathematical, structural" as a substrate claim | Made by an instrument that could only observe value-space. Yesterday's slope-field finding falsifies it as a general claim. |
| "K_G is not substrate-derivable" | Phase E tested one route (Path A) and failed. Path B was not attempted. The campaign goal remains research-grade open. |
| The 4-channel StructuredReading as the substrate-as-probe instrument | Missing the slope-space channel. The instrument synthesised in Phase F is incomplete. |
| Magic-number thresholds in Phase F decision rule | Calibrated against value-space data only; need recalibration with proper toolkit. |
| Phase H's E-as-K_G-cousin characterisation as a complete statement | Within-fixture only; whether α relates to K_G cross-fixture is unasked. |

